{
  "text": "\u2022 In the noiseless case, i.e. = 0, if the GR condition is satisfied, then\u03b2 GDDS is able to exactly recover \u03b2 * . Note that the GR condition is weaker than the RIP condition for Q = X [CITATION_1] . In other words, the RIP condition leads to GR condition when Q = X. The detailed interpretation is provided in Appendix.",
  "correct_citation": {
